I have an enum: `public enum Foo { None, One, Two }`

I want to use that enum as the options for `MudSelect`, but I don't want to show `None` in the select when the user hasn't selected a value. I want the select to be empty so that the user is required to make a selection. Is there a way to accomplish this?

```
<MudSelect Label="Foo" @bind-Value="ViewModel.Foo" Variant="Variant.Outlined">
	@foreach (Foo item in Enum.GetValues(typeof(Foo)))
		{
		<MudSelectItem Value="@item">@item</MudSelectItem>
		}
</MudSelect>
```

