I have been trying to bind mudblazor datepicker to a DateTime property using Date.

```
<MudDatePicker Label="Start Date" Date="@StartDate" />
<MudTextField Label="SelectedDate" @bind-Value="@StartDate" />
<MudText Typo="Typo.h3">Selected Date is: @StartDate</MudText>

@code
    {
        public DateTime StartDate { get; set; }
        public string DateString { get; set; }
    }
```
I have tried this code on try Mudblazor site and in visual studio. The code will update the Date Picker and my Text output when writing a valid date and leaving the text field, this is normal behavior. However, I want to change the Text based on my selection of Date picker. I have tried binding to date and value. both don't reflect the selection I have made.

I have checked the documentation on the site and there is nothing on how to handle binding beyond what I am doing.

Am I missing something or this is a bug? for now I am marking this as a Question it is very likely that I am missing something obvious.
Please help.

