Usage (this is a unit test component):
You get the MouseEventArgs, the MudTr and the item of that row via the event args

```c#
@using MudBlazor;
@using MudBlazor.Components.Table
@namespace MudBlazor.UnitTests

<MudTable T="int" Items="items" OnRowClick="@(args => OnRowClicked(args))">
    <HeaderContent>
        <MudTh>#</MudTh>
    </HeaderContent>
    <RowTemplate>
        <MudTd>@context</MudTd>
    </RowTemplate>
</MudTable>

<p>
    @(string.Join(",",clicked_items))
</p>

@code {
    public static string __description__ = "The row click event should fire, regardless of the selection events.";

    int[] items = new int[]{0,1,2};
    List<int> clicked_items = new List<int>();

    private void OnRowClicked(TableRowClickEventArgs<int> args )
    {
        clicked_items.Add(args.Item);
    }

}
```
